main event: A civilian commercial pilot observed eight disc-shaped objects flying faster than a B-29 airplane over Spokane, Washington on July 26, 1949.
interesting points: The objects were initially mistaken for jet aircraft due to the sound they made., The observer was able to see only one aircraft, a B-29, which was flying at a lower altitude., The reported altitude of the sighted objects was estimated at 14,500 feet., The pilot of the B-29 confirmed he did not see any unusual sights during the flight., The sighting occurred in good visibility conditions with broken clouds.
witness description: The witness was a civilian commercial pilot.
